   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" subtype="diplomatic" xml:id="rasm0001.diplomatic" corresp="#rasm0001.transcription #rasm0001.translation">
            <p>ΘΑΡΣΙ<lb/>
                    ΜΑΡ<lb/>
                    ΗΣ<lb/>
                    Μ
                </p>
         </div>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" subtype="transcription" xml:id="rasm0001.transcription" corresp="#rasm0001.diplomatic #rasm0001.translation">
            <p>θάρσι<lb/>
                    Μάρ<lb/>
               <unclear>ης</unclear>
               <lb/>
               <unclear>μ</unclear>´
                </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="rasm0001.translation" corresp="#rasm0001.diplomatic #rasm0001.transcription">
            <p>Be of good courage, Mares! Forty years old.
                </p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The reading of this inscription is uncertain due to erosion of the stone. In particular, the eta of line 3 could be a mu, and the sigma could be an omicron. (The name Μαρμο, however, is not attested.) Line 2 might have contained an additional one or two letter(s). The mu in the fourth line indicating the age of the deceased, here assumed to be overlined, could actually be a pi. Dimensions refer to entire remainder of stone.</p>
         </div>
